article.headline: Xavier 93, Morehead State 76
article.story: CINCINNATI (AP) -- Romain Sato scored 32 points to lead Xavier to a 93-76 victory over Morehead State on Tuesday night. Sato was 6-of-12 on 3-pointers and a perfect 7-of-7 from close range. Anthony Myles added 14 points, Dedrick Finn 13 and Lionel Chalmers 12 for the Musketeers (7-4). Ricky Minard and Chez Marks each scored 18 for Morehead State (4-6). Chad McKnight added 16 points. It was a night for sharpshooters. Morehead State hit all 10 free throws, including five by Minard. Both teams shot 57 percent from the field, but Xavier scored 25 points on 20 Eagles turnovers. Xavier built a 45-30 lead by halftime, and widened that to 32 points in the second half. It was the first time the teams played each other since Jan. 5, 1980.
